data.title: Weezer ready to paint Palace of Auburn Hills 'Red'
data.meta_description: Weezer is set to perform Monday at the Palace of Auburn Hills. AUBURN HILLS, Michigan -- Weezer drummer Pat Wilson is riding his bicycle near Lincoln Boulevard and Colorado Avenue in Santa Monica, Calif., on his way to rehearsal --...
data.text:
AUBURN HILLS, Michigan -- Weezer drummer Pat Wilson is riding his bicycle near Lincoln Boulevard and Colorado Avenue in Santa Monica, Calif., on his way to rehearsal -- and he couldn't be any happier about it.

"It's going well," Wilson said about rehearsal as he shouts in his cellphone over traffic. "It's fun getting back into it after not playing in this fashion for about 2 years. It's fun to get back at it."Weezer -- which also includes vocalist/guitarist Rivers Cuomo, guitarist Brian Bell and bassist Scott Shriner -- is rehearsing for its major arena tour in support of its self-titled, Rick Rubin-produced release, also known as "The Red Album" for its jacket hue. The jaunt, which comes to The Palace of Auburn Hills on Monday, features support act Angels and Airwaves.

Concert preview:

Weezer with special guest Angels and Airwaves

• When: 7:30 p.m. Monday

• Where: The Palace of Auburn Hills

• Tickets: $45, $39.50 and $25

• Details: (248) 645-6666 or go online.
